body:
Rep Tour night 2

Once night 1 was over, I was so excited I got to relive it again on night 2.

This time I was pitch seating and I was going on my own. I was sitting beside two lovely girls from Canada called Jessica and Jenny. They were visiting Ireland a d decided to go. They where impressed with my knowledge of Taylor which was cool.

During Taylor’s second song, I was busy singing and dancing but for some reason I took my eye of the stage and looked in front of me and I stopped dead in my tracks, Andrea was stood less than 5 feet from me, I couldn’t believe it. I didn’t know what to do, then I decided I would say hello but I couldn’t get out from my seat so I shouted towards her but she couldn’t hear me and she walked if into the crowd. I was devastated. I spent the next few songs trying to see if I could see her again but it wasn’t to be.

When Delicate cane on I ran down towards the back of the pitch seating to the railings between the stages. I knew Taylor would be walking through here from the first night. She sang the surprise song which was ‘How you get the girl’ and then started her walk through the crowd.

I was hoping she would grab my hand but it really is a lottery. I was one of the lucky ones as she grabbed my hand when she walked by. I couldn’t believe it. There was a little girl beside me tgat got handed a guitar pick too which was lovely.

I made my way back to my seat for the rest of the concert. The ending was so good with 'This is why we can’t have nice things’ and the fireworks where so cool. It was just amazing.

For anyone going to future dates, you are going to have the best time.

body:
Rep Tour Dublin night 1

I was so excited for this concert. It felt like I was waiting for ages. The day finally arrived. We got to the stadium very early, shortly after gates opened. We where sat in the middle tier of the stand. From our seats we could see the route the acts took to get from their dressing rooms to the stage. At one point I seen Andrea with a group of people backstage and I am not gonna lie, I was pretty jealous.

Charlie XCX came on first and she was really good. Really got the crowd going and was very energetic.

Camilla was next and although I didn’t know many of her songs she was still good. She sand a really nice version of ‘Can’t help falling in love’.

Finally it was time for Taylor. She gave us a wave with the biggest smile on her face while making her way to the stage. I won’t give out any spoilers for those that haven’t seen it yet but it was everything I expected and more. The surprise song was 'Mean’ which was a nice surprise.

When it was over I was delighted I had bought tickets for night two as well.

That’s my story of night 1.

summary: Dear Taylor I‘m so excited for the show in Wembley London Night 1. Seeing the bracelets, the lights, the dancers, the musics,...
body:
Dear Taylor

I‘m so excited for the show in Wembley London Night 1. Seeing the bracelets, the lights, the dancers, the musics, the stages, the fireworks and snakes  (something that scares me a lot but for Taylor I will overcome this fear), the amazing crowds, the fans meeting Andrea and you @taylorswift, and YOU  @taylorswift.

I could make a list about the fears that I’ll overcome to see you: fireworks, snakes and the worst, the flight. I’m not used to flight is for that that I’m a little afraid.

But the most important thing about this is that I’ll do this effort economic and psychological for see you @taylorswift and for see my sister @crswift living one of the best days of her life. You @taylorswift has helped her a lot with anxiety problems, you are her lifeline. The last year was one of our worst years with the dead of two grandparents in less than a month. We need to say thank you and hug you.

We are flying from Spain for second time only to see you again but we pray and hope that this time we could meet you. Sometimes I lost my hope because we are millions of swifties and all deserve to meet you @taylorswift, and it’s impossible that you meet all in one day.

If you @taylorswift or someone of @taylornation or maybe @tree-paine read this I hope that you make come true our dream and special the dream of my sister @crswift. I know that we are many swifties but like your song says…don’t you dream impossible things?

Thank you my dear @taylorswift
